WHEREAS, Ascension Parish Day at the state capitol serves as a celebration of this
shared success and vision and brings together more than eighty businesses, nonprofits,
governmental and community partners, first responders, and educational institutions to
showcase the parish's impact and potential; and
WHEREAS, the event at the Capitol Park Museum highlights not only the
achievements of the past and present, but also the promise of a bold and collaborative future.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
designate Wednesday, April 22, 2026, as Ascension Parish Day at the state capitol; does
hereby honor the past accomplishments, present momentum, and future promise of
Ascension Parish; does hereby recognize its commitment to growth, partnership, and
building a better tomorrow; and does hereby encourage citizens, partners, and stakeholders
to celebrate the collective efforts that make Ascension Parish a model of collaboration,
progress, and opportunity.
